        "question_Vz8Mai": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Here’s a practical “match-by-use-case” guide:</p><ul><li><strong>Best all-around folding, high comfort, and strong brakes</strong>:<br/><strong>Hunter Pro</strong> – Features <strong>full suspension</strong>, <strong>dual hydraulic brakes</strong>, <strong>95 Nm</strong> of torque, <strong>48V 15Ah</strong> battery, up to <strong>80 miles</strong> range, and <strong>400 lb</strong> payload. Perfect for long rides across varying terrain.</li><li><strong>Best value folding fat tire for mixed terrain</strong>:<br/><strong>X-Hunter</strong> – A <strong>folding model</strong>, with <strong>85 Nm</strong> of torque, <strong>48V 13Ah</strong> battery, and up to <strong>70 miles</strong> range. Great for riders seeking an affordable but versatile fat tire eBike.</li><li><strong>Best step-through accessibility and hydraulic brakes</strong>:<br/><strong>X-Hunter ST</strong> – A <strong>low-step frame</strong> model with <strong>dual hydraulic brakes</strong>, <strong>up to 71 miles</strong> range, and <strong>480 lb</strong> payload capacity. Ideal for easy mounting and urban commuting.</li><li><strong>Best 26\" platform for taller riders and long-range battery</strong>:<br/><strong>Thunder Pro</strong> – With <strong>26\" x 4\" tires</strong>, a <strong>52V 20Ah</strong> battery, <strong>dual hydraulic brakes</strong>, and up to <strong>90 miles</strong> of range, this is the go-to for riders looking for stability at higher speeds and rougher roads.</li><li><strong>Fastest moped-style eBike with 52V system</strong>:<br/><strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong> – Featuring <strong>full suspension</strong>, <strong>52V 20Ah</strong> battery, up to <strong>90 miles</strong> range, and speeds up to <strong>38 mph</strong> with pedal assist, this is ideal for those seeking maximum speed and comfort.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "question_azW6Lx": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Yes, fat tire eBikes excel in snow, sand, and gravel due to their <strong>wide tire width</strong> that allows for better <strong>traction</strong> and <strong>flotation</strong>. Fat tires help you maintain stability on soft and uneven surfaces, reducing the risk of sinking into the terrain.</p><p>For snow or sand, it’s common to <strong>lower tire pressure</strong> slightly to improve grip, while for pavement, <strong>higher PSI</strong> reduces rolling resistance and improves efficiency. If you frequently ride in <strong>winter conditions</strong>, models like <strong>Hunter Pro</strong> (full suspension + dual hydraulic brakes) or <strong>Thunder</strong> <strong>Pro</strong>(26\" x 4\" tires) are excellent choices.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_BVTA9m": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Top speed varies by model (and local regulations). On JasionBike’s product specs:</p><ul><li><strong>Hunter Pro</strong>: <strong>30+ mph</strong> </li><li><strong>X-Hunter</strong>: <strong>30+ mph</strong></li><li><strong>X-Hunter ST</strong>: <strong>30+ mph</strong> </li><li><strong>Thunder Pro</strong>: <strong>35 mph</strong> </li><li><strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong>: up to <strong>38 mph</strong> (with pedal assist per the listing)</li></ul><p>Always ride within your local eBike class/speed rules.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_3xmeW9": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Most of JasionBike's fat tire models, including the <strong>Hunter Pro</strong>, <strong>X-Hunter</strong>, <strong>X-Hunter ST</strong>,   <strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong>, and <strong>Thunder Pro</strong>, use <strong>cadence sensors</strong>. A <strong>cadence sensor</strong> detects the rate of pedaling (how fast you’re pedaling) and adjusts power output accordingly, providing a smoother, more consistent assist—ideal for <strong>casual rides</strong> or <strong>commuting</strong>.</p><p>If you're seeking a more <strong>natural ride feel</strong>, <strong>torque sensors</strong> (which detect pedal force) are generally found on higher-end models.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_YDF4n7": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Payload capacity is critical for larger riders and anyone carrying gear.</p><p>From the published specs:</p><ul><li><strong>X-Hunter ST</strong>: up to <strong>480 lbs</strong></li><li><strong>Hunter Pro / X-Hunter</strong>: up to <strong>400 lbs</strong></li><li><strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong>: up to <strong>330 lbs</strong></li><li><strong>Thunder Pro</strong>: up to <strong>500 lbs</strong></li></ul><p>Remember: payload includes rider + accessories + cargo.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_WfwAxR": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Hydraulic brakes matter for confident stopping—especially on heavier fat tire eBikes.</p><p>Models that list <strong>dual hydraulic brakes</strong> include:</p><ul><li><strong>Hunter Pro</strong></li><li><strong>X-Hunter ST</strong></li><li><strong>Thunder Pro</strong></li><li><strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong></li></ul><p>If you’re choosing between two similar bikes, hydraulic brakes are a strong “quality-of-ride” upgrade.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "question_igw8xT": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>JasionBike primarily uses:</p><ul><li><strong>20\" x 4\" fat tires</strong> on models like <strong>Hunter Pro</strong>, <strong>X-Hunter</strong>, <strong>X-Hunter ST</strong>, and <strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong>—great for compact storage and agile handling. </li><li><strong>26\" x 4\" fat tires</strong> on <strong>Thunder Pro</strong>—more rollover and stability on rough roads and at speed. </li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "question_tnHrzy": {
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Torque (Nm)</strong> is what you feel when accelerating, climbing, or pushing through soft terrain. <strong>Motor power (W)</strong> influences sustained output and top-end performance, but torque often better predicts “hill confidence.”</p><p>Here’s a breakdown from JasionBike's models:</p><ul><li><strong>Hunter Pro</strong>: <strong>95 Nm</strong> of torque</li><li><strong>X-Hunter</strong>, <strong>X-Hunter ST</strong>: <strong>85 Nm</strong> of torque</li><li><strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong>: <strong>99 Nm</strong> of torque</li><li><strong>Thunder Pro</strong>: <strong>115</strong> <strong>Nm</strong> of torque</li></ul><p>If you ride in <strong>hilly or off-road areas</strong> or carry heavy loads, models with higher torque like <strong>Hunter Pro</strong> or <strong>RetroVolt Pro</strong> will offer better performance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_6jw9hm": {
